{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh spinach into it, then set aside.","Place 1000 g of the water into mixing bowl and heat <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add pasta and 1 teaspoon of the salt and 1 teaspoon of the oil and cook <b>8-10 min\/98°C\/\/speed 1<b>, until cooked to your liking. Using simmering basket, drain pasta, then transfer into thermal serving bowl with spinach and cover to keep warm.","Place garlic, onion and remaining 1 teaspoon oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add pepitas and 60 g of the water and cook <b>6 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add nutritional yeast, tahini, thyme, basil, lemon juice, flour, pepper, milk, remaining ½ tsp salt and remaining 60 g water and blend <b>40 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides and bottom of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mushrooms and cook <b>4-6 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer sauce into thermal serving bowl with pasta and stir to combine. Garnish with cheese and parsley to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g fresh baby spinach leaves","1120 g filtered water","250 g dried fettuccine (egg free - see Tips)","1 ½ tsp salt","2 tsp extra virgin olive oil","3 garlic cloves","½ brown onion (approx. 90 g)","40 g pepitas (see Tips)","20 g nutritional yeast (see Tips)","1 tbsp tahini (see Tips)","¼ tsp dried thyme","½ tsp dried basil","2 tsp lemon juice","1 tbsp sorghum flour","1 pinch ground black pepper","350 g plant-based milk of choice","200 g fresh brown mushrooms, cut into thin slices (5 mm)","2 tbsp vegan Parmesan cheese (see Tips)","fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only, chopped, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r341384","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-WIpQbowmb7s\/XZVRYQZFRJI\/AAAAAAAAdNw\/brK-x7ZhP_gUe2JTZqA2otQXjKNtWWiLQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nXnZlwdeXJDY3Gsn.png","title":"Pasta Alfredo with mushrooms","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.6 g","fat":"18.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.9 g","calories":"1435.9 kJ \/ 341.9 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the pepitas with 3-4 tablespoons of cashews, if desired.","With a cheesy, umami flavour, nutritional yeast contains all nine essential amino acids, is a great source of B vitamins and is often fortified with vitamin B12 (important for those following a vegan diet). You can find nutritional yeast at health food stores or online.","To make your own tahini, refer to the recipe on Cookidoo® (www.cookidoo.com.au).","To make your own vegan Parmesan cheese, refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","You can replace the pasta with raw or blanched vegetable zoodles, if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","4 portions"]}